<h4 id="thinking-about-thinking">Thinking about thinking</h4>

<p>There are different methods to attack a problem, usually called mental models. These tools are frameworks of thinking that humans have made to approach solutions.</p>

<h4 id="reductionism-">Reductionism ğŸ’¡</h4>

<p>For example, Elon Musk has his favorite framework of thinking: <em>the first principles</em>. This model can be classified as a reductionist method.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>First Principles consist in break a whole problem into small parts. This approach helps Elon back then in the early years when he wanted to create a cheaper and more accessible rocket compared to the Russians. Yes, this was the story behind SpaceX.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Iâ€™m a big fan of reductionist thinking. We can adopt it when we are study statistical models. It is helpful to see each part of a linear regression and how <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nk2CQITm_eo">itâ€™s composed</a>.</p>

